    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-06T04:41:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-06T04:41:00-05:00" n="506"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/323</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-06T11:00:00+01:19">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1918, 11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 12.32 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2271. Your assurances in regard to the <hi rend="italic">Prinses Juliana</hi>, as
                    referred to in your 1070, March 29, and 1073, March 30,<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d506fn1">The latter not printed.</note> are negatived by a
                    semiofficial report in the papers this morning that this steamer has been seized
                    at Hongkong. Grave doubt is thus cast, not perhaps on the good faith, but
                    certainly on the value of our assurances. May I deny this report before it goes
                    any further?</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Garrett</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
